  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dinner rolls baked close together on a tray share heat and steam with each other, which is why the sides stay soft and pull apart easily. If you bake them with space between them, you get rolls with a crust on all sides. Both are good; this recipe goes for the pull-apart, shared-table version."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ingredients"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
